.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tmagazine.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/04/29/10-of-the-moment-rufus-wainwright/|title=10 of the Moment \u2013 Rufus Wainwright|accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018 Green was a recipient of the [[American Humanist Association]]'s Humanist Arts Award<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Bradley |first1=Andrew |last2=Green |first2=Deven |title=Parodies of Power: Why Satire Is Needed Now More Than Ever |journal=The Humanist |date=2018 |volume=78 |issue=6 |pages=25\u201328 |url=https://thehumanist.com/magazine/november-december-2018/features/parodies-of-power-why-satire-is-needed-now-more-than-ever |accessdate=22 August 2019 |quote=Here, adapted from their remarks in acceptance of the American Humanist Association's 2018 Humanist Arts Award, presented at the AHA annual conference on May 19 in Las Vegas NV is presented.|issn=00187399}}</ref>\n\n=== Voice work ===\nShe was the original movie-listing voice for Cineplex Odeon theatres in Canada.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}} Green was the voice for the Canadian versions of [[The Walt Disney Company|Walt Disney]] commercials. Deven is currently an [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|A.D.R.]] and commercial voice artist.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}}\n\n=== Print and modelling ===\nGreen has been a panel member of ''[[Star (magazine)|Star]]'' magazine's weekly Style Squad since May 2012.\n\nThe nail lacquer colour Deven Green was released by OCCmakeup at [[Sephora]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sephora.com/product/productDetail.jsp?keyword=deven%20green&skuId=1601624&productId=P377412&_requestid=121716 |title=Nail Lacquer \u2013 Obsessive Compulsive Cosmetics |publisher=Sephora |date= |accessdate=2014-03-23}}</ref>\n\nShe also appeared as a spokesmodel for OCCmakeup's 2014 Spring Collection \"Plastic Passion\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.temptalia.com/occ-automaton-deven-green-pool-boy-nail-lacquers-reviews-photos-swatches |title=OCC Automaton, Deven Green, Pool Boy Nail Lacquers Reviews, Photos, Swatches |